15 independence. Each such marker shall honor the two-hundred and fiftieth anniversary of
16 the United States and those who fought for the noble cause of liberty and for a new nation.
17 (b) Placement location for Revolutionary War Patriots markers provided for in this Code
18 section shall be subject to approval by the Capitol Arts Standards Commission for
19 placement upon the grounds of the state capitol building and by the Board of Regents for
20 the placement of the marker upon the grounds outside the state archives building.
21 (c) No public funds shall be expended for the design or procurement of the markers
22 provided for in this Code section. Each such marker shall be placed as soon as practicable."
23 SECTION 2.
24 All laws and parts of laws in conflict with this Act are repealed.
